      "explanation": "Vertical translation — f(x) + k shifts the graph up k units; f(x) − k shifts it down. Horizontal translation — f(x − h) shifts the graph right h units; f(x + h) shifts it left. The other options — 'Down 3 units', 'Right 3 units', and 'Left 3 units' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
